The paper discusses the learning of good representations through the interaction between unsupervised and reinforcement learning modules, which falls under the category of machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also mentions the use of intrinsic motivation, which is a common topic in artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The focus on object recognition suggests that computer vision (cs.CV) is another likely sub-category. The use of simulated environments suggests that robotics (cs.RO) may also be relevant. Finally, the use of reinforcement learning suggests that neural networks (cs.NE) may also be relevant.
